headline: Why UnitedHealth Stock Imploded Last Month
summary: UnitedHealth Group continued its historic drop in May, losing 26.6% during the month.  The health insurer is facing new allegations of fraud and misconduct.  Shares of UnitedHealth Group (NYSE: UNH) fell in May, finishing the month down 26.6%.

headline: 3 Reasons We’re Fans of UnitedHealth (UNH)
summary: What a brutal six months it’s been for UnitedHealth. The stock has dropped 46.3% and now trades at $303.30, rattling many shareholders. This was partly due to its softer quarterly results and may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
